Powershell CLI window keeps repeating and restaring in a loop

Powershell CLI window keeps repeating and restaring in a loop, the directory keeps repeating and doesnt stop even if killed, i have curated a workaround by directly bypassing the inbuilt powershell and configured the system's powershell in Open User Setting(JSON) with: "terminal.integrated.profiles.windows": {
 "PowerShell": null,
 "Windows PowerShell": null,

 "PowerShell (clean)": {
 "source": "PowerShell",
 "args": ["-NoProfile"]
 },
 "Command Prompt": {
 "path": "C:\\Windows\\System32\\cmd.exe"
 }
 },
 "terminal.integrated.defaultProfile.windows": "PowerShell (clean)"

Please honor the RuntimeHint parameter

Describe the feature or problem you’d like to solve
The OpenAI json spec has a parameter "runtimeHint" to tell the client what command to use when setting up the mcp server declaration from an MCP Registry.
Please update VSCode so that it honors this field.
My company uses Podman instead of Docker for container management locally and this seems like the way to change the docker command to a podman command.

Proposed solution
VSCode honors the runtimeHint parameter from the OpenAI spec so that I can set Podman as the image runner instead of Docker.

Example prompts or workflows (for tools/toolsets only)
"packages": [
{
"registryType": "oci",
"identifier": "",
"runtimeHint": "podman",
"transport": {
"type": "stdio"
},
"environmentVariables": [
{
"description": "Gitlab access token",
"isRequired": true,
"name": "GITLAB_TOKEN"
}
]
}
],
